<descript>       <abstract>Data available online through GeoStor at http://www.geostor.arkansas.gov.  The Digital Raster Graphic (DRG) is a raster image of a scanned USGS topographic map, georeferenced to the  UTM grid.</abstract>       <purpose>A DRG is useful as a source or background layer in a  GIS, as a means to perform quality assurance on other digital products, and as a source for the collection and revision of DLG data.  DRG's can also be merged with other digital data, e.g. DEM's or DOQ's, to produce a hybrid digital file.</purpose>       <langdata Sync="TRUE">en</langdata>       <supplinf>This information is provided as is</supplinf>     </descript>     <timeperd>       <timeinfo>         <rngdates>           <begdate>19770101</begdate>           <begtime>unknown</begtime>           <enddate>19970102</enddate>         </rngdates>       </timeinfo>       <current>ground condition</current>     </timeperd>     <status>       <progress>Complete</progress>       <update>Irregular</update>     </status>     <keywords>       <place>         <placekt>None</placekt>         <placekey>United States</placekey>         <placekey>Arkansas</placekey>       </place>       <theme>         <themekt>ISO 19115 Topic Category</themekt>         <themekey>imageryBaseMapsEarthcover</themekey>       </theme>       <theme>         <themekey>drg</themekey>         <themekey>topo</themekey>         <themekey>contours</themekey>         <themekey>contour</themekey>         <themekey>elevation</themekey>         <themekt>Arkansas Geographic Information Office</themekt>         <themekey>drgs</themekey>         <themekey>drgs</themekey>         <themekey>quad</themekey>         <themekey>map</themekey>       </theme>     </keywords>     <ptcontac>       <cntinfo>         <cntorgp>           <cntorg>U.S. Geological Survey</cntorg>           <cntper>Robin D.
